77":"1377","1498":"1498","1485":"1485","1480":"1480","1380":"1380","1407":"1407","Acton and Old Felton, Northumberland, England":"Acton and Old Felton, Northumberland, England","Alnwick, Northumberland, England":"Alnwick, Northumberland, England","Old Felton, Northumberland, England":"Old Felton, Northumberland, England","Northumberland, England":"Northumberland, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Acton","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of several places, especially in Shropshire and adjacent counties, named Acton. Generally, these are from Old English <i>āc</i> ‘oak’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘settlement’. In Ireland the surname has been established in Connacht since the 17th century."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Lawrence","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Anglicized spelling of   Laurence .  This is the usual spelling of the surname, and is now becoming increasingly common as a given name, especially in North America."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":52,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Lawrence Acton was born in 1403, in Acton and Old Felton, Northumberland, England, his father, Richard Acton, was 26 and his mother, Elizabeth Sturmyn, was 23. He married Matilda de Echingham in 1426, in Old Felton, Northumberland, England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1480, in his hometown, at the age of 77."},"et":{"1403–1480":"1403–1480","1407–1485":"1407–1485","1424–1498":"1424–1498","1377–Male":"1377–Surnud","1380–Female":"1380–Surnud","25 July 1424":"25. juuli 1424","1426":"1426","1403":"1403","1424":"1424","1400":"1400","1455":"1455","1377":"1377","1498":"1498","1485":"1485","1480":"1480","1380":"1380","1407":"1407","Acton and Old Felton, Northumberland, England":"Acton and Old Felton, Northumberland, England","Alnwick, Northumberland, England":"Alnwick, Northumberland, England","Old Felton, Northumberland, England":"Old Felton, Northumberland, England","Northumberland, England":"Northumberland, England"},"fi":{"1403–1480":"1403–1480","1407–1485":"1407–1485","1424–1498":"1424–1498","1377–Male":"1377–Kuollut","1380–Female":"1380–Kuollut","25 July 1424":"25. heinäkuuta 1424","1426":"1426","1403":"1403","1424":"1424","1400":"1400","1455":"1455","1377":"1377","1498":"1498","1485":"1485","1480":"1480","1380":"1380","1407":"1407","Acton and Old Felton, Northumberland, England":"Acton and Old Felton, Northumberland, England","Alnwick, Northumberland, England":"Alnwick, Northumberland, England","Old Felton, Northumberland, England":"Old Felton, Northumberland, England","Northumberland, England":"Northumberland, England"},"fr":{"1403–1480":"1403–1480","1407–1485":"1407–1485","1424–1498":"1424–1498","1377–Male":"1377–Décédé","1380–Female":"1380–Décédée","25 July 1424":"25 juillet 1424","1426":"1426","1403":"1403","1424":"1424","1400":"1400","1455":"1455","1377":"1377","1498":"1498","1485":"1485","1480":"1480","1380":"1380","1407":"1407","Acton and Old Felton, Northumberland, England":"Acton and Old Felton, Northumberland, Angleterre","Alnwick, Northumberland, England":"Alnwick, Northumberland, Angleterre","Old Felton, Northumberland, England":"Old Felton, Northumberland, Angleterre","Northumberland, England":"Northumberland, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Sir Lawrence Acton est né en 1403, à Acton and Old Felton, Northumberland, Angleterre, son père, Richard Acton, avait 26 ans et sa mère, Elizabeth Sturmyn, avait 23 ans. Il a épousé Matilda d’Echingham en 1426, à Old Felton, Northumberland, Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille. Il est décédé en 1480, dans sa ville natale, à l’âge de 77 ans."},"de":{"1403–1480":"1403–1480","1407–1485":"1407–1485","1424–1498":"1424–1498","1377–Male":"1377–Verstorben","1380–Female":"1380–Verstorben","25 July 1424":"25. Juli 1424","1426":"1426","1403":"1403","1424":"1424","1400":"1400","1455":"1455","1377":"1377","1498":"1498","1485":"1485","1480":"1480","1380":"1380","1407":"1407","Acton and Old Felton, Northumberland, England":"Acton and Old Felton, Northumberland, England","Alnwick, Northumberland, England":"Alnwick, Northumberland, England","Old Felton, Northumberland, England":"Old Felton, Northumberland, England","Northumberland, England":"Northumberland, England","lifeSummary":"Als Sir Lawrence Acton 1403 in Acton and Old Felton, Northumberland, England geboren wurde, war sein Vater Richard Acton 26 und seine Mutter Elizabeth Sturmyn 23. Er hat 1426 in Old Felton, Northumberland, England Matilda de Echingham geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Tochter. Er starb 1480 im Alter von 77 Jahren in seinem Geburtsort."},"ht":{"1403–1480":"1403–1480","1407–1485":"1407–1485","1424–1498":"1424–1498","1377–Male":"1377–Desede","1380–Female":"1380–Desede","25 July 1424":"25 July 1424","1426":"1426","1403":"1403","1424":"1424","1400":"1400","1455":"1455","1377":"1377","1498":"1498","1485":"1485","1480":"1480","1380":"1380","1407":"1407","Acton and Old Felton, Northumberland, England":"Acton and Old Felton, Northumberland, England","Alnwick, Northumberland, England":"Alnwick, Northumberland, England","Old Felton, Northumberland, England":"Old Felton, Northumberland, England","Northumberland, England":"Northumberland, England"},"hu":{"1403–1480":"1403–1480","1407–1485":"1407–1485","1424–1498":"1424–1498","1377–Male":"1377–elhunyt","1380–Female":"1380–elhunyt","25 J